                     "solar eclipse": ["A solar eclipse is an astronomical phenomenon that occurs when the Moon is a crescent while passing between the Earth and the Sun. The Moon causes the Sun to be partially or completely blocked from the Earth. Total solar eclipses occur at least twice a year, and can be seen with the naked eye from a few areas on the Earth's surface. These points are only about 150 kilometers wide²³. It is advisable not to look directly at the Sun during an eclipse to avoid permanent eye damage or blindness. Special techniques can be used to protect the eyes or enjoy viewing the eclipse in indirect ways.",],


