               "lunar eclipse": ["A lunar eclipse is an astronomical phenomenon that occurs when the Earth's shadow blocks the sunlight reflected on the Moon in normal conditions. A lunar eclipse occurs when the Moon is in the full phase, and the Moon is in a straight line with the Sun and the Earth. This alignment causes the Moon to enter the Earths shadow, which blocks the Sun's light from the Moon. A lunar eclipse occurs completely, completely, or partially, depending on the position of the Moon, the Earth, and the Sun. A lunar eclipse is an exciting and interesting phenomenon for astronomical observers and those interested in astronomical phenomena.",],



