                "penguin": ["Well! Penguins are aquatic birds that do not fly. They belong to the penguin family and live in the southern hemisphere. There are few penguins that live in temperate regions, and only one species lives in the equator, which is known as the Galapagos penguin. Penguins weigh between 1.5 kg and 14 kg, and are between 43 cm and 122 cm long. As for lifespan, penguins live from 6 to 30 years. Penguins live in the water and use their wings to dive and catch fish and other seafood. They are the only bird that walks on land and dives underwater.",],

