                      "frog": ["Frogs are vertebrates of the amphibian family, and belong to the group Anurans. The word in Greek means tailless. Frogs are characterized by their short, soft bodies and long hind legs. Their fingers are connected by thin membranes that help them swim, and they do not have a tail. Most frogs live in a semi-aquatic environment and move by jumping. They lay their eggs in streams, ponds and lakes, and have gills that help them breathe in water. Adult frogs feed on arthropods, annelids and gastropods. They can be noticed by their croaking sounds at night or during the day or during periods of sexual estrus. Frogs are found all over the world, from tropical to semi-cold regions. It is believed that there are more than 5,000 species of frogs, and they are among the most widespread vertebrates. There is also a frog-like amphibian called a toad, which lives far from water and lacks the skill of jumping.",],



