"when did world war 1 start": ["World War I, also known as the Great War, was an international conflict that began in July 1914 and ended in November 1918. This war involved more than 70 countries and resulted in more than 16 million casualties. The war began with the assassination of Archduke Franz Ferdinand of Austria in July 1914, and expanded to include many countries. The Allied Powers, Britain, France, Russia, Italy, Romania, Japan, and the United States, faced the Central Powers, Germany, Austria-Hungary, the Ottoman Empire, and Bulgaria. The war was caused by political, economic, and military tensions between European countries, and the escalation of military alliances and colonial rivalries. The war broke out after the assassination of Archduke Franz Ferdinand in Bosnia and Herzegovina, and expanded to include several continents and resulted in radical changes in politics. ",],

"world war 2": ["World War II was a devastating international conflict that began on July 7, 1937 in Asia and September 1, 1939 in Europe and ended in 1945 with the surrender of Japan. About seventy countries participated in it, and the main armed forces were divided into the Allied and Axis powers. World War II witnessed important battles such as the Battle of Stalingrad, the Battle of the Japanese Islands, the Battle of Normandy, and the Battle of the Mediterranean. Causes of the war include the Treaty of Versailles, the events of World War I, the rise of Adolf Hitler, the German-Soviet Pact, revanchism, fascism, chauvinism, the Holocaust, and the atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki. This war resulted in massive casualties among military and civilian personnel, with more than 17 million people killed. ",],

"when did world war 2 start": ["World War II was a devastating international conflict that began on July 7, 1937 in Asia and September 1, 1939 in Europe and ended in 1945 with the surrender of Japan. About seventy countries participated in it, and the main armed forces were divided into the Allied and Axis powers. World War II witnessed important battles such as the Battle of Stalingrad, the Battle of the Japanese Islands, the Battle of Normandy, and the Battle of the Mediterranean. Causes of the war include the Treaty of Versailles, the events of World War I, the rise of Adolf Hitler, the German-Soviet Pact, revanchism, fascism, chauvinism, the Holocaust, and the atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki. This war resulted in massive military and civilian casualties, with more than 17 million people killed. ",],

"cold war": ["The Cold War is a state of conflict between states that does not involve direct military action, but is pursued primarily through economic and political measures, propaganda, espionage, or proxy wars waged by agents. It began in the mid-1940s and lasted until the early 1990s. The two major powers in this conflict were the United States and the Soviet Union, and the world was divided into two camps: the communist camp led by the Soviet Union and the liberal camp led by the United States. The Cold War witnessed international crises such as the Berlin Blockade, the Korean War, the Berlin Crisis of 1961, the Vietnam War, and the Cuban Missile Crisis. In the late 1980s, the Soviet Union collapsed, leaving the United States as the sole superpower in a unipolar world.",],




                "من هو مخترع التلفاز": ["تطورت تكنولوجيا التلفاز لأول مرة في القرن التاسع عشر، حيث اخترع الألماني فرديناند براون أنبوب أشعة الكاثود في عام 1897 للميلاد، واستخدم أنبوب أشعة الكاثود لأول مرة لإنتاج الصور عام 1907م. ثم تبع ذلك التطويرات المستقلة لكل من الإنجليزي فيلو فارنسورث والروسي فلاديمير زوريكين. في العشرينيات من القرن العشرين، حصل الإسكتلندي جون لوجي بيرد على براءة اختراع لفكرة استخدام مجموعة قضبان شفافة في نقل صور التلفاز. بيرد كان أول شخص يعرض صورًا متحركة على التلفاز. أما التلفاز الإلكتروني، فقد تم اختراعه من قبل الأمريكي فيلو فارنسورث في العام 1927م، حيث استخدم أنبوبة تفريغ لإنتاج الصور إلكترونيًا على شاشة حساسة للضوء. في العام 1900م، ظهرت كلمة ,تلفاز, لأول مرة في معرض باريس من قبل الفرنسي كونستانتين بيرسكي",],





