                   "who invented the car": ["All historians agree that the first car was invented by a man named Nicolas-Joseph Cugnot, from France. In 1769, Cugnot worked on inventing the first car that could seat four people and was powered by steam. This car was a huge three-wheeled bicycle, and it moved for 20 minutes continuously, then stopped to renew the steam energy to move again. It traveled about 2.25 miles per hour, or about 3.6 km. A replica of Cugnots car is in the National Institute of Arts and Crafts in Paris.",],

